Backend engineer & open source tinkerer. Author of logdrop. I like small tools that do one thing well.

:NOW
Stabilising v1.4.0 — patches welcome, big features go to the v2.0 milestone.

:INFO
What is logdrop?
logdrop is a zero-dependency CLI that sits between your process and your observability stack.
Pipe any stdout/stderr into it and it will tail, filter by log level or regex, and forward
structured JSON to a local file, a webhook, or a cloud sink (Datadog, Loki, CloudWatch).

It ships as a single static binary. No runtime. No config file required for basic use.
Drop it on a server, point it at a process, and you're done in 30 seconds.

:QUOTE
Your logs should go where you need them, not where your framework decided.

